## config.ts — env accessors

Use these functions from `src/lib/wordpress/config.ts`; never read `process.env` directly in fetcher files:

| Function / Accessor         | Returns                                    |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `getWordpressApiUrl()`      | REST base URL (e.g. `https://wp.site.com`) |
| `getWordpressBaseUrl()`     | WP home URL (may differ from API URL)      |
| `getSiteUrl()`              | `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`                     |
| `getCptRestBase(cpt)`       | REST base for CPT: `service`, `testimonial`, `case_study` — reads from env or defaults |
| `getHomepageSlug(lang)`     | Lang-specific homepage slug                |
| `getBlogPageSlug(lang)`     | Blog archive slug segment (default `blog`) |
| `getCaseStudyArchiveSlug(lang)` | Case study archive slug (default `case-studies`) |
| `getMenuId(location, lang)` | WP menu ID from env for a menu location    |
| `getDefaultContactFormId()` | `NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_CF7_FORM_ID`          |
| `getRevalidationSecret()`   | `REVALIDATION_SECRET`                      |

